                <h4>What is the voting age population of Buffalo, Texas?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Buffalo, Texas, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 1,205.  The voting age population is 43.2% male and 56.8% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, Texas residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 14.1% of
                        the residents of Buffalo are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Buffalo, Texas?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Buffalo are 83.5% White, 12.5% Black, 2.0% Two or more races, 1.5% American Indian and 0.5% Asian. Additionally, 29.9% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, Texas residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Buffalo, 27.9% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 49.0%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    19.0% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Buffalo.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, Texas residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 56.0% of
                    Buffalo residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Buffalo, Texas residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    78.3% of
                    Buffalo residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 8.2%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 4.4%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, Texas residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Buffalo residents aged 5 and older, 28.6% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                26.6% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                0.5% speak an Indo-European language, and
                1.5% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Buffalo, Texas?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Buffalo is 6.7%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Buffalo, Texas residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Buffalo, 13.6% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Buffalo, Texas?</h4>
